  "sections": {
    "Background": {
      "text": "Mortality is extremely rare after intentional overdose if good supportive care is provided\nRapid IV dosing carries greatest risk (due to propylene glycol constituent of IV form → myocardia depression & cardiac arrest)\n90% protein bound; dialysis ineffective",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "CV (only with IV form)\nBradycardia\nHypotension\nVfib\nAsystole\nNeuro\nNystagmus\nFirst only with forced lateral gaze; later becomes spontaneous\nMay disappear at higher levels\nAtaxia\nDecreased LOC\nGI\nNausea and vomiting\nSkin\ntissue infiltration (IV) → \"\nPurple glove syndrome\n\"\nedema, pain, ischemia, tissue necrosis,\ncompartment syndrome\nAnticonvulsant hypersensitivity syndrome\nFever\n,\neosinophilia\n,\nrash\n, pseudolymphoma,\nSLE\n,\npancytopenia\n,\nhepatitis\n,\npneumonitis\n,\npharyngitis\n,\nrhabdomyolysis\nMortality rate of 10%",
      "subsections": {},
