    "Management": {
      "text": "Supportive care is mainstay of treatment\nIf intubation needed, standard RSI meds ok, avoid lidocaine (same antidysrhythmic properties as phenytoin)\nIf symptomatic bradyarrhythmia:\nACLS: Bradycardia\n, Atropine, epinephrine, dopamine are first line\nMay consider\ntranscutaneous\nor\ntransvenous pacing\nHypotension\nIVF bolus\nDetoxification\nActivated charcoal\nPO\nGastric lavage\nand\nwhole bowel irrigation\nare\nNOT\nrecommended",
